721562f-a.title: Manhattan: Maiden Lane - Front Street
721562f-a.text:
Maiden Lane, west from and including Front Street (across the foreground), showing what appears to be a tobaoco center at this location. This thoroughfare which derived its name from the Dutch, divides at a point above Gold Street to form in addition Liberty Street (left). The large structure forming the apex at that point is the Great American Insurance Company Building. To the left of same is the 24 storied Fire Companies Building. Note the Singer Building
tower (with flag atop) in the background.
October 1914.
George L. Balgue.

719909f-a.title: Manhattan: Front Street - Maiden Lane
719909f-a.text:
160 Front Street, west side, from Maiden Lane to Fletcher Street, showing the 7-story building of the New Jersey Einc Comupany. The photograYer is viewing same,westward on Maiden Lane from a point between South and Front Streets. At the right is the silhouetted New York Steam Company chimney outlined against the
35-story office building, No. 1 Platt Street.
June 16, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Snerr
